      {
        "annotationType": "ANNOTATION",
        "comment": {
          "commentType": "FUNCTION",
          "texts": [
            {
              "value": "Involved in the restart of stalled replication forks, which reloads the replicative helicase on sites other than the origin of replication; the PriA-PriB pathway is the major replication restart pathway. During primosome assembly it facilitates complex formation between PriA and DnaT on DNA; stabilizes PriA on DNA. Stimulates the DNA unwinding activity of PriA helicase"
            }
          ]
        }
      },
      {
        "annotationType": "ANNOTATION",
        "comment": {
          "commentType": "SIMILARITY",
          "texts": [
            {
              "value": "Belongs to the PriB family"
            }
          ]
        }
      },
      {
        "annotationType": "ANNOTATION",
        "comment": {
          "commentType": "SUBUNIT",
          "texts": [
            {
              "value": "Homodimer. Interacts with PriA and DnaT. Component of the replication restart primosome. Primosome assembly occurs via a 'hand-off' mechanism. PriA binds to replication forks, subsequently PriB then DnaT bind; DnaT then displaces ssDNA to generate the helicase loading substrate"
            }
          ]
        }
      },
